				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Why do all pets(save fire) have almost identical melee abilities??  They all quad and for similar damage. 
<br />

<br />
A suggestion: Turn Rathe's son into a 2 Hand style pet.
<br />

<br />
Rathe's Son(current w/DPOC): quads for 81, bashes and kicks
<br />
Rathe's Son(new w/DPOC): doubles for 175, no bash, but kicks
<br />

<br />
I know this isn't much of an "upgrade", but it would help when fighting mobs with damage shields, and reduce riposte damage pets take and increase the riposte damage they deliver. This is more in line with "give pets some variety" rather than "make pets stronger". Just something I've been pondering.  /shrug<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=705852" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Nucci(Inactive)</a>
<br />

