			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Take it from me, you don't want to change the pets from quadding to double attacking 2hander style.  A long time ago while bst pets were being 'fixed' from the bundle of fur following us they used to be, they changed bst pet melee to be more like Bst melee skills in an attempt to fix their botched h2h skills.  Along with it came no double attack (for a pet with no mainhand damage bonus, it really didn't matter wither they were DAing with only mainhand or DW with no DA, you could only tell the difference by giving the pet 2 different types of weapons).  So, even though they gave the pet a serious attack boost and it hit for max very often, it's lowly 2 attacks per round gave identical DPS as the broken quadding pet.
<br />

<br />
Pets already are immune to riposte since shortly after PoP was released (seeing as even teir 1 mobs had a nasty habit of riposting misplaced pets to death in just a few rounds, and 100x more of them enraged on a normal basis than those that are left).  By requesting a 2 hand using pet, it seems to me it would cause more problems than it is worth, as they would inevitably break the pets far more than fix them when they would start poking around with max hits, base attack, and swing delay.  Stick with simply wanting a higher base attack and higher max hit, among the many defensive changes mage pets need.  Those will get better results w/o allowing the devs to break mages further for a while, heh heh.
<br />

<br />
Elder Longfanz Beaztmaster Feral Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
