			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pets do have a small chance of taking a riposte hit.  If you think otherwise, pay more attention to your pet's health bar during a boss enrage -- if your pet is engaging the mob from the front.  He takes a hit or two, but not nearly as many as a PC melee would, given a similar number of landed attacks.
<br />

<br />
Likewise, They can take regular ripostes as well, but have a very small chance of being hit, so it's not that big a deal.  The patch message for this change actually said that pets had a <span style="font-style: italic">reduced chance</span> of being hit by a riposte, not that they were immune to them.  
<br />

<br />
The real bonus to increased weapon damage would be when then pet itself is enraged, and is, itself, riposting.  Another benefit would be that the flurry AA would get to do alot more damage, since (if I recall correctly), flurry is a check done on the primary hand only.  This is assuming the delay of the non-dual-wielding pet is identical to the delay of the regular pet, of course.
<br />

<br />
Yet another benefit of such a change would be that the insane damage shields of some GoD bosses would be less ridiculous -- not to the point of being sane, but less ridiculous in any case.<br />_________________<br />Arhallia Ironborne
<br />
<span style="color: red">65th Arch Convoker</span>
<br />
Toenan Twosoks
<br />
<span style="color: green">56th Animist</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue"><span style="font-weight: bold">Alliance of the Arcane</span></span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Quellious server</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
