				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pet riposte is indeed fairly frequent as you can test by /pet hold,/pet guarding vs. a mob. Jobaber sit there quietly regenning while the mob beats on him and every tick or two throws out a melee-riposte hit.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes when I am being lazy, I will /pet hold,/pet guard jobaber on a gimp (eg. Chardok / Sebilis level) mob, and go make a cup of coffee. The combination of DS/riposte attacks/270hp-per-tick regen lets the pet smack down the pet without risk.
<br />

<br />
