			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">samxp wrote:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">You sounded as if pets doesn't take enrage. 
<br />
Pets still takes enrage riposte. Just to clarify.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
No, I was pointing out one of the secondary changes made to the lower level PoP zones at the same time they changed that pets no longer take riposte damage.  If you played in PoP, even teir 1, when it was first released, you would know that(for example) common courtyard bugs in PoD enraged probably 9 out of 10 kills.  Between the fact that so many mobs that ranged from 51-56(something new with PoP that was seldom seen in the older expansions) had the ability to enrage, and that the mobs now hit for x3+ the amount people were used to fighting, ripostes were literally tearing up PC's and pets alike.  They downgraded the average mob's riposte ability, and made pets immune to riposte so that mages weren't having to run around behind the mob every 2 seconds to reposition Jabober so that they wouldn't have to make a new pet or spend a ton of mana on heals each fight instead of doing damage to the mob.  Granted, all pet classes' pets were dealing with this issue though.
<br />

<br />
I never implied pets don't take enrage damage.  Enrage and riposte are 2 very different things, regardless of the riposte message you get while attacking from the from during enrage.  Enrage is more like a warrior's riposte /disc, that has basically been hard-coded for certain mobs to use at appx 10% health.  
<br />

<br />
Also, no pets are not 'somewhat' immune to enrage.  Having played quite a few melee classes, I understand that there aren't just 2 spots to an enraged mob, as in enraged from the front and autoriposted vs. able to attack from the rear with no fear of enrage ripostes.  There is also a small side window on a mob that you cannot attack an enraged mob on.  While you can swing at the mob, you will recieve the riposte message as if you were attacking from the front, but you will take no riposte damage.  It's only about a 20 degree angle on either side, but most likely you are seeing the mob's postition slightly(if you haven't hit /pet hold already knowing the mob would enrage, or reposition Jabober to the rear) change during enrage causing the pet to sometimes slip out of that angle and into the frontal enrage window and take damage, then back into the side window where he will take no damage but still recieve the riposte message.  I know it sounds odd, but ask any melee and they will tell you the same if they have any experience with mobs that enrage.
<br />

<br />
Elder Longfanz Beaztmaster Feral Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
